article.headline: Wecker double-double fills bill
article.linkText: Wecker paces Wildcats over Saint Josephs
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Kendra Wecker scored 21 points and had 14
rebounds to lead Kansas State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today; No. 22 AP) past Saint Joseph's 68-49
Thursday night.
	   Wecker made 9-of-16 shots and Laurie Koehn added 11 points for
the Wildcats (8-2).
	   Kansas State led 36-30 with 14:12 left before an 11-0 run over
the next 5 minutes increased its lead to 47-30. The Hawks (2-10)
did not make a field goal for the first 10:45 of the second half.
	   Over that span, Saint Joseph's missed nine shots while making
7-of-8 free throws.
	   The Hawks, who have lost seven straight games, were led by Maura
McBryan with 12 points. Ayahna Cornish added 10 points.
	   Kansas State won its fourth straight and outrebounded Saint
Joseph's 48-25.
